message.text:
Long Message ahead RE: Mcgraw Hill Connect fees 😀

eto na naman ako sa feelings ko and I know I'm posting this purely out of frustration and disappointment, but I won't feel this way kung di ko nararamdaman na parang ghinoghost kami ng FEU regarding concerns about our McGraw Hill Connect sa canvas. Please allow me to just express this out as I’d like to share something that might resonate with how you’re feeling too, especially if you also want to hold FEU accountable. If not, feel free to skip this post. 
Apart from the blended learning setup concerns/complaints that are being raised, this Mcgraw Hill Connect for IAS and IABF is also one of the concerns that needs to be addressed because of the sudden ₱850 that we have to pay just to avail it and guess what? it's only accessible to us for 1 year. Don't get me wrong, this McGraw Hill Connect is actually helpful for me as a psych student, but what I don't understand is bakit kailangan bayaran or magdagdag bayarin parin kami even if our tuition was raised to ₱71,000.00?(di pa yan yung accurate tuition fee ah) Given the fact na blended learning na nga kami for this semester, so the expenses for the school would be lesser, beneficial for all students and faculty, bonus na din is to help the facilities of the university become better (since andaming renovations and andami pang nasisira) I don't understand san pa napupunta yung ₱71,000.00 when infact shouldn't this McGraw Hill payment be taken from the miscellaneous fees that is part of the tuition?? 

What gets me more frustrated is that there's no proper orientation nor formal announcements from the people incharge about this (kung meron man, hindi umaabot samin and madami din kaming mga 3rd year na nagtatanungan na lang sa isa't isa to clarify things about the payment and if ₱850 per subject nagagamiting ang McGraw which for the record combining all 3 or more subjects it would be ₱2,550+. O diba? pwede na yan sa miscellaneous fees). 
Gulatan na lang sa orientation na "oh access niyo McGraw Hill niyo ah that is what we'll use for this semester. Not sure if there will be a code sent or if kasama sa tuition niyo, but the book that we'll use is there, sabi magkakaroon din ng orientation about it and hopefully you'll get your code bago mag expireyung temporary access." Pati profs kinakapa ano ang magiging system for this McGraw Hill setup. Like come on, it's already the 3rd week of the semester and yet still nothing about this aside from answering the undertaking and some students already having their temporary access expire by today or tonight (which would delay or be an obstacle with their participation in class kasi may quizzes doon) tapos we'll be met with this na idadagdag yung permanent 1 year access namin sa tuition? We don't even have the option to say No kasi we know that we need it, but why does our need as students always have to come with a price tag or at a high expense?. Yung pag pindot ko pa sa form na "I agree" is labag pa sa loob ko. 

Come on FEU, where is the Excellence that your school upholds when it comes to providing accessible yet good quality education? I've given you enough benefit of the doubt that you'll do better, make better plans for your students since you'd always expect the best from
us students, but for the most part all you ever did was ignore our concerns for
what we need by putting a price on or upping the price on everything, not sticking to your words nor hearing your students out through the surverys regarding their concerns yet pressure us to become the best even with a flawed system, and leaving us be to figure it out on our own just to get kasi sa huli kayo din naman palagi ang masusunod. 
All we ask for is transparency, accountability, and an open, inclusive educational environment — one that offers high-quality learning without compromising accessibility for anyone.
Nagbabayad naman kami, all you have to do is do YOUR PART in providing us good and fair education. Ayusin niyo naman sistema niyo sa ganito please.

body.text:
Hello, dear! I’m Sam, the President of FEU Psychology Society.

Thank you for bringing this to our attention. We want to start by acknowledging your frustration and that it is completely understandable to be concerned about the extra costs, especially when you are already managing so many other expenses as a student. Please know that we are taking this matter with the utmost seriousness and urgency.

We have received concerns regarding this matter since last Saturday and immediately raised the issue with the department. However, since Sunday and today, Monday, are non-working days for the university offices, we are currently awaiting their official response. Rest assured, we have made it very clear that this is a top priority for us. We are actively advocating for you and all Psychology students.

We believe that no student should be left behind due to financial constraints. While we wait, we are exploring every possible avenue for a quick resolution. In the meantime, we strongly encourage you to speak with your respective professors tomorrow. They might have already received updates or could provide you with an alternative solution to access the learning material. Your professors are a great resource and we believe they will be more than willing to assist you.

We are committed to finding a solution that benefits everyone and will keep you updated as soon as we have more information available on our end provided by the Psychology department.

Thank you!
